 Troops of 271 Nigerian Air Force (NAF) Detachment, Birnin Gwari dismounted an ambush set up by armed bandits at Kawan Pole Waya, about 20km from Birnin Gwari along the Kaduna-Birnin Gwari Road.   According to a statement made available to newsmen by the Director of Public Relations and Information Air Commodore Ibikunle Daramola, the troops were able to fight their way through the ambush to the side of Birnin Gwari and called for reinforcement. Daramola said 2 NAF personnel unfortunately who paid the supreme price in the process are Flying Officer Abdulrahman Bayero and Aircraftman Saidu Bawa, and are scheduled to be buried today in accordance with Islamic rites.   The Chief of the Air Staff (CAS), Air Marshal Sadique Abubakar, on behalf all officers, airmen, airwomen and civilian staff of the NAF, commiserates with the families of the fallen heroes and prays that the Almighty grants their souls’ peaceful repose.